agents describes osx-run
osx-run creates a reproducible macOS build environment on Linux
the script installs osxcross, Python 3.11, and Node 22, sets cross-compilation variables, and adds osx-run to PATH
usage
1. download osx-run.sh and make it executable
2. run osx-run.sh install osxcross to prepare the toolchain
3. optionally run osx-run.sh install python 3.11 and osx-run.sh install node 22
4. run osx-run.sh <command> to use the prepared environment
